# ASG Admin Hub — Cursor Rules

## Project Context
This is a collection of self-contained HTML/CSS/JS code blocks for the Alex Stoykov Group (ASG) Admin Hub, a real estate team dashboard hosted on Squarespace. Each component file in `components/` is a standalone code block that gets pasted directly into a Squarespace Code Block injection point.

## Tech Stack
- **Hosting**: Squarespace (Code Block injections)
- **Frontend**: Vanilla HTML + CSS + JavaScript (no build step, no frameworks)
- **Fonts**: Google Fonts — prefer **Outfit** for new UI per brand brief; **Poppins** (400–800) remains in existing components until migrated
- **Data Sources**: Google Apps Script web apps (JSON APIs), Google Sheets (published CSV)
- **External Services**: Google Drive, Asana forms, Acuity Scheduling (as.me)

## Architecture Rules
- Every component is a **single self-contained file** (HTML + `<style>` + `<script>`)
- No external JS/CSS files — everything is inline within the code block
- All CSS is scoped via unique prefixes to avoid Squarespace collisions:
  - Dashboard: `asg-h-` prefix
  - Team Directory: `asg-dir-` prefix
  - Listing Hub standalone: `lh-` prefix
  - Marketing Assets: `asg-admin-assets__` prefix
  - Agent Cards: `admin-` prefix
- IIFEs `(function(){ ... })()` wrap all JS to avoid global scope pollution
- `window._asg*` and `window._lh*` functions are the only intentional globals (for onclick handlers in generated HTML)

## Data & API Endpoints
- **Stats API**: `https://script.google.com/macros/s/AKfycbzC8TWq.../exec` — returns pipeline stats (volume, deals, agents)
- **Folders API**: `https://script.google.com/macros/s/AKfycbwrDNg.../exec` — returns recent Google Drive listing photo folders
- **Listings API (v1)**: `https://script.google.com/macros/s/AKfycbyt2jh.../exec` — listing hub data (active/archive)
- **Listings API (v2)**: `https://script.google.com/macros/s/AKfycbzCDWt.../exec` — listing hub with email/share support
- **Buyers CSV**: Google Sheets published CSV (gid=1143085145)
- **Sellers CSV**: Google Sheets published CSV (gid=1110212825)

## Team Roster
The team roster (TEAM array) is duplicated across components. The canonical list is in `shared/team-data.js` for reference. When updating team members, sync changes across:
1. `admin-dashboard.html` (and v2)
2. `team-directory.html`
3. `agent-cards.html`
4. `listing-hub-standalone.html` (agent email map)

## Coding Conventions
- Use `var` in standalone listing hub (broader browser compat); `const/let` in dashboard components
- HTML escaping via `esc()` helper for all user-facing data
- Phone numbers cleaned via `telClean()` — strips non-digit chars
- Currency formatting via `fmt()` — $1.2M / $450K / $1,200
- Mobile detection via `isMobile()` for adaptive click actions (copy vs mailto/tel)
- All images have `onerror` fallbacks to initials placeholders

## Design System
**Authoritative visual spec:** `../docs/ASG-DESIGN-SYSTEM-BRIEF.md` — modern luxury minimal, bento layouts, monochrome-first, generous spacing, pill controls, subtle borders over heavy shadows, restrained accents. Follow the brief for all new or redesigned UI; match existing component prefixes and escape patterns.

**Legacy implementation snapshot** (existing components; align refactors to the brief):
- Border radius: ~24–32px major containers / ~28px cards, 999px pills, 14–18px compact actions
- Shadows: faint only; prefer thin borders where possible
- Colors: #111 primary, muted grays; use accents sparingly (e.g. #3b82f6, #22c55e, #eab308, #f97316, #8b5cf6) for status/emphasis
- Font weights: 400 body, 600 labels, 700 buttons/names, 800 headings/values
- Animations: subtle only — fadeIn, barGrow, popIn/popOut, shimmer (loading), pulse (live)

## Deployment
Changes are deployed by copying the full file contents and pasting into the corresponding Squarespace Code Block. There is no build step. See `../docs/DEPLOYMENT.md` for the mapping.
